verbs.description: overlabour (third-person singular simple present overlabours, present participle overlabouring, simple past and past participle overlaboured)

entries.meaning: (transitive) To cause to labour excessively; to overwork.
examples: over-labour'd with so long a course,'Tis time to set at ease the smoking horse

entries.meaning: (transitive) To labour upon excessively; to refine unduly.
